**Responsive CSS Grid:**

**Answer:** `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(100px, 1fr))`

**Complete Responsive Grid Methods:**

**1. Auto-fit with minmax:**
```css
.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
}
```

**2. Auto-fill with minmax:**
```css
.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 15px;
}
```

**3. Media Queries for Different Breakpoints:**
```css
.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 10px;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
    .grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
}
```

**4. Fractional Units:**
```css
.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
}
```

**5. CSS Grid with CSS Variables:**
```css
.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(var(--columns, 1), 1fr);
    gap: var(--gap, 1rem);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
    .grid {
        --columns: 2;
        --gap: 2rem;
    }
}
```

**Key Differences:**
- **auto-fit:** Collapses empty tracks
- **auto-fill:** Keeps empty tracks
- **minmax():** Sets minimum and maximum sizes
- **fr:** Fractional unit for flexible sizing

**Adding Items to CSS Grid:**

**Complete Grid Placement Methods:**

**1. Individual Properties:**
```css
.item {
    grid-row-start: 1;
    grid-row-end: 3;
    grid-column-start: 1;
    grid-column-end: 5;
}
```

**2. Shorthand Properties:**
```css
.item {
    grid-row: 1 / 3;
    grid-column: 1 / 5;
}
```

**3. Span Properties:**
```css
.item {
    grid-row: span 2;
    grid-column: span 3;
}
```

**4. Grid Area (Named Areas):**
```css
.item {
    grid-area: row-start / col-start / row-end / col-end;
}
```

**5. Grid Area with Named Areas:**
```css
.container {
    grid-template-areas:
        "header header header"
        "sidebar main main"
        "footer footer footer";
}

.item {
    grid-area: header;
}
```

**Complete Grid Placement Values:**

**Grid Row/Column Values:**
- `1` - Line number
- `1 / 3` - Start / End
- `span 2` - Span 2 tracks
- `auto` - Auto placement
- `-1` - Last line
- `-2` - Second to last line

**Grid Area Values:**
- `header` - Named area
- `1 / 1 / 3 / 4` - Row-start / Col-start / Row-end / Col-end
- `auto` - Auto placement

**Grid Gap:**
- `grid-gap: 20px` - Space between all items
- `row-gap: 10px` - Space between rows
- `column-gap: 15px` - Space between columns

**CSS Grid Template Areas:**

**Complete Grid Template Areas Guide:**

**1. Basic Setup:**
```css
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-areas:
        "header header header"
        "sidebar main main"
        "footer footer footer";
}
```

**2. Item Placement:**
```css
.item-1 { grid-area: header; }
.item-2 { grid-area: sidebar; }
.item-3 { grid-area: main; }
.item-4 { grid-area: footer; }
```

**Complete Grid Template Areas Rules:**

**Area Naming Rules:**
- Use single quotes for each row
- Each row must have same number of areas
- Use dots (.) for empty areas
- Use same name for spanning areas

**Area Values:**
- `header` - Named area
- `main` - Named area
- `.` - Empty area
- `sidebar` - Named area
- `footer` - Named area

**Grid Template Areas Examples:**

**1. Basic Layout:**
```css
.container {
    grid-template-areas:
        "header header header"
        "sidebar main main"
        "footer footer footer";
}
```

**2. Complex Layout:**
```css
.container {
    grid-template-areas:
        "nav nav nav nav"
        "sidebar main main aside"
        "sidebar main main aside"
        "footer footer footer footer";
}
```

**3. Empty Areas:**
```css
.container {
    grid-template-areas:
        "header header header"
        ". main main"
        "footer footer footer";
}
```

**4. Responsive Areas:**
```css
.container {
    grid-template-areas:
        "header"
        "main"
        "footer";
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container {
        grid-template-areas:
            "header header"
            "sidebar main"
            "footer footer";
    }
}
```

