**Add width and height:**

```css
.square {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
}
```

**Key points:**
- Set both `width` and `height` to the same value
- Use any unit: `px`, `em`, `rem`, `%`, `vh`, `vw`
- The element will become a perfect square

**Example:**
```css
/* Rectangle */
.rectangle {
    width: 300px;
    height: 100px;
}

/* Square */
.square {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
}
```

**Single Line Text:**
```css
.single-line {
    line-height: 50px;  /* Same as height */
    text-align: center;
    height: 50px;
}
```

**Multi-line Text:**
```css
.multi-line {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    height: 100px;
}
```

**Alternative for multi-line:**
```css
.multi-line-alt {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    height: 100px;
}
```

**Key differences:**
- **Single line:** Use `line-height = height`
- **Multi-line:** Use `display: flex` with `align-items: center`

