**CamelCase Naming Convention**

**Format:**
- Start with lowercase letter
- Capitalize the first letter of each new word
- No spaces or underscores

**Example:**
```javascript
weWriteItLikeThis
```

**Common uses:**
```javascript
var firstName = "John";
var lastName = "Doe";
var myAge = 25;
var userEmailAddress = "john@example.com";

function calculateTotalPrice() {
    // code here
}

function getUserData() {
    // code here
}
```

**Why use camelCase:**
- Standard convention in JavaScript
- Easy to read without spaces
- Distinguishes variables from constants (UPPER_CASE)
- Distinguishes from classes (PascalCase)

