answer:
**While and For Loops (Numbers 1-10)**

**While Loop:**
```javascript
var myArr = [];
const i = 0;
while(i <= 10){
    myArr.unshift(i); // or myArr.push(i)
    i++;
}
console.log(myArr);
```

**For Loop:**
```javascript
var myArr = [];
for (var i = 1; i <= 10; i++){
    myArr.unshift(i);
}
console.log(myArr);
```

**Key differences:**
- **While loop:** Checks condition first, then executes
- **For loop:** Initializes, checks condition, executes, then increments
- **unshift():** Adds to beginning of array
- **push():** Adds to end of array

