**Counting Backward with Loops**

**For Loop (Backward):**
```javascript
var myArr = [];
for (var i = 100; i > 0; i-=2){
    myArr.push(i);
}
console.log(myArr);
```

**While Loop (Backward):**
```javascript
var myArray = [];
let j = 50;
while(j > 0){
    myArray.push(j);
    j-=3;
}
console.log(myArray);
```

**Key concepts:**
- **i-=2:** Decrements by 2 each iteration
- **i > 0:** Condition checks if greater than 0
- **Starting high:** Begin with large number, count down
- **Decrement:** Use -= instead of += for backward counting

