**var vs let Differences**

**Main difference:**
- **var:** Can be redeclared in the same scope
- **let:** Cannot be redeclared in the same scope

**Scope differences:**
- **var:** Has function scope (or global scope)
- **let:** Has block scope (limited to { } blocks)

**Examples:**
```javascript
// var can be redeclared
var x = 5;
var x = 10; // This works

// let cannot be redeclared
let y = 5;
let y = 10; // This causes an error
```

**Scope example:**
```javascript
// var scope
if (true) {
    var a = 1;
}
console.log(a); // 1 (accessible outside block)

// let scope
if (true) {
    let b = 1;
}
console.log(b); // Error! b is not accessible
```

